    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How to Move a Fleet in C4 PTR" class="article-title">
          How to Move a Fleet in C4 PTR
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2026-06-03T13:56:20Z" title="2026-06-03T13:56:20Z" data-datetime="relative">June 03, 2026 13:56</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/52273962138771-How-to-Move-a-Fleet-in-C4-PTR/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>Fleet movement allows you to travel between locations in the Galia Expanse.</p><p>In C4 PTR, fleets can move using different movement options depending on distance, speed, fuel, and available routes.</p><blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> C4 PTR is still in development. Movement rules, costs, travel times, and available routes may change over time.</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6VTK3SAX72CAQ0XP3YYWQZ">Before you start</h2><p>Before moving a fleet, make sure:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="ed855ee992d5243456ff0cdc828c2e51e">Your fleet has been created.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ed3e5fe94417e9043820353eb3c116847">Your fleet is undocked.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ebea76974ea7e00fb472d4c0f13f34a76">Your fleet has the required fuel or access to the selected travel method.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e469f7bdafd6dcc391b29a9483d7458d1">You have selected the fleet from the map or from the <strong>My Fleets</strong> menu.</li>
</ul><p>If you have not created a fleet yet, check the <a href="/hc/en-us/articles/52251721868563"><strong>How to Create and Use a Fleet in C4 PTR</strong></a> guide first.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6VPTMT1RSWMJFEMSG57NZS">Fleet movement options</h2><p>Depending on your fleet and destination, you may see different movement options.</p><p>The main movement options are:</p><ul>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="ef4ddcc766412b394e969c2d81a6a58ce"><strong>Warp</strong></li>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="e17a0819ad38d58651d167fa8a260a480"><strong>Subwarp</strong></li>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="e0900cb0fab87f1e9794120d31ebacf4c"><strong>Warp Gate</strong></li>
</ul><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 673/200;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52273980055827" width="673" height="200"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6VPTMVWEW51MDZ1XD2QEE6">Subwarp</h2><p><strong>Subwarp</strong> is used to travel longer distances, but it is slower than Warp.</p><p>To use Subwarp:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="edc97fded07d3bfdbc332d9682de9349d">Select your fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="efb97db5af1bef9f0b8ae24bb0e83d4e0">Click <strong>Subwarp</strong> from the fleet action menu.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="efbe9c1a562d3997c82d6a9c3252d58e1">Move your mouse over the map to choose a destination.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e386ef50b2a89157f38aae9aea0c637b6">
<p>Review the movement preview, including travel distance, ETA, and fuel consumption.</p>
<figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1860/1505;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52273980056723" width="1860" height="1505"></figure>
</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e1a4f51d2d8fa92ccb91212e1983a8d1e">Click your destination.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ed9ae9cb3051a0fba3c69ee1a00625d5d">
<p>Click <strong>Start Subwarp</strong> at the bottom of the screen.</p>
<figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1896/1516;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52273980057619" width="1896" height="1516"></figure>
</li>
</ol><p>&nbsp;</p><h3 id="h_01KT6VPTMYAHF6RCTNHFSTCP49">Tip for long-distance Subwarp</h3><p>If you want to move farther away:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="ee909777c29033693f7f78113a0ad9d73">Zoom out using your mouse wheel.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea5ffba48acf13544c8f7cc00f1470981">Move around the map until you find the area you want to reach.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e1f6e0a18f186d74bc05ff9699f07b853">Zoom back in if needed.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ed3fd3c4c66999b7f583cbd3ba480da45">Select your destination.</li>
</ol><p>This makes it easier to choose a destination that is farther from your current location.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6VPTN0NXE97ZMG27W32512">Warp</h2><p><strong>Warp</strong> is faster than Subwarp, but usually works over shorter distances and consumes more fuel.</p><p>To use Warp:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="ee4a6993754fb112b4cb58e11ccb79dfe">Select your fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ec94bc1dcbdf8575577c121c803905016">Click <strong>Warp</strong> from the fleet action menu.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3e96e67096137a6112edaa3e3fd9a619">Choose your destination on the map.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ed4ba12c73638a69f1f903058b0feb02c">Review the travel information.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eca0c6a858a088e76f6eedeba8b69dc98">Confirm the movement order.</li>
</ol><p>Warp is useful when you want to move faster and your destination is within available Warp range.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1992/1482;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52273980058387" width="1992" height="1482"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6W7F6J3NF709Y3FZ2F20G4">Warp Gate</h2><p>Warp Gate travel is different from normal fuel-based movement:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e93c9b0b976427b3fd4848d3d356e31c6">It is very fast.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ebc622c1026f15f368185f1d6f1dc61bb">It costs ATLAS.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3d679acc72c5afc53eb459e4558c65a8">It does not consume normal fleet travel resources.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e1756acf5fdbd9fe08650bf2ceb849247">It is limited to accessible gates.</li>
</ul><p>Warp Gate travel can be used when the required route is available, such as when your faction controls the relevant start and destination regions.</p><p>To use a Warp Gate:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e516e230ae1854bd9d23fbc55c77e983f">Select your fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e64113ab792a6d84e93649306de815bd9">Click <strong>Warp Gate</strong> from the fleet action menu.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e77d5670018f0a85926e2fdd6123a27ac">Review the list of available gates.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e029d4fbaf38533473d875358f665f876">Check the ATLAS cost and travel time.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e30cb561c1ffded15cafbf2bca354943b">Select the gate destination.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e7ef6f95edaf84e36faae204b0baee1b4">Confirm the travel order.</li>
</ol><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 629/580;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52273980059795" width="629" height="580"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6W925ZSEDEQ437PZ83DDHB">Summary</h2><p>To move a fleet in C4 PTR:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="ec3c020b0d31065fad20d352374644176">Select an undocked fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e9d118557974ff07ae5ba6c7c952a8031">Choose a movement option: <strong>Warp</strong>, <strong>Subwarp</strong>, or <strong>Warp Gate</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e9904e4d7764450f014f59400fe0bec7f">Select a destination.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ef1e55f1b9e08f2d3b9e1fef54db2d0b3">Review the ETA, distance, and cost or fuel consumption.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3229ca656a0fe3ee568b975540727e78">Confirm the movement order.</li>
</ol><p>Use <strong>Subwarp</strong> for longer, slower travel.<br>Use <strong>Warp</strong> for faster travel over shorter distances.<br>Use <strong>Warp Gate</strong> when an available gate route exists and you want fast travel using ATLAS.</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

